				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Do these glitches happen on reads or writes? I'm thinking at least reads, because for example the PowerPak would be used almost always for reads from ROM. In that case, it would be the fast RAM chip's bus buffer driving the data bus, which has the capacitance of all the other chips on it. The fast RAM chip drives with more current, so it puts more load on the power bus. If it's not sufficiently decoupled, then I believe it'll see glitches on its inputs. This is a little beyond my experience, based on recent readings.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

